@coolsday- Unpacking the release means taking the files you download from the torrent and making them in the format that is used to play the game. So when you see DVD1 and DVD2 in the spot where you downloaded this torrent (probably in downloads), unpack it by downloading winrar, opening it, then extract the data. When you click the extract data, just browse to DVD1 and click on the first file in the folder. Do the same for DVD2.

For mounting the data, download Daemontools lite for free. There will be a little icon down on the bottom right hand side of the screen on the taskbar, with a blue lightning bolt. Left click it then select Device 0:(F:) no media. Then click on the .iso file that you unpacked earlier, it should be in DVD1 and it will trick the computer into thinking that you have the mw2 disk :) Then, when the game asks for disk 2, just mount the second .iso file in DVD2.


